These are the minutes for the June 13th, 2022 SPI Board Meeting,
held at 20:00 UTC in #spi on irc.spi-inc.org.
[LOG](../../../logs/2022/2022-06-13-log.txt).

## President's Report

Michael Schultheiss was not present.

Stephen Frost gave an update as Vice President:

<pre>
We continue to work with our contractors to move things forward, in
particular the new membership system and also getting off of the old
systems and on to the new ones.

We recently chatted w/ Gandi and it sounds like they're open to
potentially helping with domains and renewals. Projects who have
domains with SPI should expect to hear from our IT contractor soon
regarding getting them set up with the Gandi group that is supporting
SPI with domain renewals.
</pre>

## Treasurer's report

<pre>
Slow progress, due to paternity. However, payments are being
processed, but there is some backlog that should be addressed end of
this week. Statements had been collected for April and May, and
website should also get updated real soon now.Audit is progressing and
we keep looking for required documentation for auditor.
</pre>

## Secretary's report

<pre>
Board elections are coming up in July. I'll be sending out the usual
email to the members list asking for nominations.Existing directors
are encouraged to reapply and we'd love to have new people on the
board as well.

I will be resigning at the conclusion of the election (one year early)
for personal reasons. I'm happy to help out anyone who would like to
take over with advice, templates etc.
</pre>

